162. Selecting with jQuery

    - Select elements with $()
      
      This is very similar to document.querySelectorAll("selectorGoesHere")
      
    - Use $(selector).css() to style elements
    
      for example: $("h1").css("color", "yellow");
      
      you can also pass an object with styles
      
      var styles = {
          backgroundColor: "orange",
          fontWeight: "bold"
      };
      
      $("#special").css(styles);
      
      Note: the properties in the styles object are camel case, not snake case
            if $() returns a collection of elements, the .css() method will auto iterate over all elements
            the style object could be defined inline the $().css expression:
            
            $("#special").css({
                backgroundColor: "orange",
                fontWeight: "bold"
            });
            
164. Text and HTML

    .text() - get or set the text content inside an element, includes children
    .html() - get or set html contents of elements, similar to .innerHTML
    
165. Attr and Val

    .attr() - get or set the value of an attribute
    .val() -- extracts the value for an element
    
166. Manipulating CSS Classes

    .addClass()
    .removeClass()
    .toggleClass()
    
    